After talking to Mike, I wanted to clarify one point.  Apparently ESA 
currently  has an employee available to manage the Stack Manager out of 
Houston.  From a tax perspective that employee can manage the Stack Manager 
out of Houston for the short duration in which ENA is trying to see if this 
is a viable product..  If that is the route that is chosen, it will be 
necessary for ESA and ENA to enter into an agreement whereby the ESA employee 
is seconded to ENA for purposes of providin these services.

Lynn




